#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_directory.rst:162
msgid ":ref:`int <class_int>` **get_drive_count** **(** **)**"
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_directory.rst:164
msgid ""
"On Windows, returns the number of drives (partitions) mounted on the "
"current filesystem. On other platforms, the method returns 0."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_directory.rst:170
msgid ":ref:`String <class_String>` **get_next** **(** **)**"
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_directory.rst:172
msgid ""
"Returns the next element (file or directory) in the current directory "
"(including ``.`` and ``..``, unless ``skip_navigational`` was given to "
":ref:`list_dir_begin <class_Directory_method_list_dir_begin>`)."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_directory.rst:174
msgid ""
"The name of the file or directory is returned (and not its full path). "
"Once the stream has been fully processed, the method returns an empty "
"String and closes the stream automatically (i.e. :ref:`list_dir_end "
"<class_Directory_method_list_dir_end>` would not be mandatory in such a "
"case)."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_directory.rst:180
msgid ":ref:`int <class_int>` **get_space_left** **(** **)**"
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_directory.rst:182
msgid ""
"On UNIX desktop systems, returns the available space on the current "
"directory's disk. On other platforms, this information is not available "
"and the method returns 0 or -1."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_directory.rst:188
msgid ""
":ref:`Error <enum_@GlobalScope_Error>` **list_dir_begin** **(** "
":ref:`bool <class_bool>` skip_navigational=false, :ref:`bool "
"<class_bool>` skip_hidden=false **)**"
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_directory.rst:190
msgid ""
"Initializes the stream used to list all files and directories using the "
":ref:`get_next <class_Directory_method_get_next>` function, closing the "
"current opened stream if needed. Once the stream has been processed, it "
"should typically be closed with :ref:`list_dir_end "
"<class_Directory_method_list_dir_end>`."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_directory.rst:192
msgid "If ``skip_navigational`` is ``true``, ``.`` and ``..`` are filtered out."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_directory.rst:194
msgid "If ``skip_hidden`` is ``true``, hidden files are filtered out."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_directory.rst:200
msgid "void **list_dir_end** **(** **)**"
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_directory.rst:202
msgid ""
"Closes the current stream opened with :ref:`list_dir_begin "
"<class_Directory_method_list_dir_begin>` (whether it has been fully "
"processed with :ref:`get_next <class_Directory_method_get_next>` or not "
"does not matter)."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_directory.rst:208
msgid ""
":ref:`Error <enum_@GlobalScope_Error>` **make_dir** **(** :ref:`String "
"<class_String>` path **)**"
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_directory.rst:210
msgid ""
"Creates a directory. The argument can be relative to the current "
"directory, or an absolute path. The target directory should be placed in "
"an already existing directory (to create the full path recursively, see "
":ref:`make_dir_recursive <class_Directory_method_make_dir_recursive>`)."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_directory.rst:218
msgid ""
":ref:`Error <enum_@GlobalScope_Error>` **make_dir_recursive** **(** "
":ref:`String <class_String>` path **)**"
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_directory.rst:220
msgid ""
"Creates a target directory and all necessary intermediate directories in "
"its path, by calling :ref:`make_dir <class_Directory_method_make_dir>` "
"recursively. The argument can be relative to the current directory, or an"
" absolute path."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_directory.rst:228
msgid ""
":ref:`Error <enum_@GlobalScope_Error>` **open** **(** :ref:`String "
"<class_String>` path **)**"
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_directory.rst:230
msgid ""
"Opens an existing directory of the filesystem. The ``path`` argument can "
"be within the project tree (``res://folder``), the user directory "
"(``user://folder``) or an absolute path of the user filesystem (e.g. "
"``/tmp/folder`` or ``C:\\tmp\\folder``)."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_directory.rst:238
msgid ""
":ref:`Error <enum_@GlobalScope_Error>` **remove** **(** :ref:`String "
"<class_String>` path **)**"
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_directory.rst:240
msgid ""
"Deletes the target file or an empty directory. The argument can be "
"relative to the current directory, or an absolute path. If the target "
"directory is not empty, the operation will fail."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_directory.rst:248
msgid ""
":ref:`Error <enum_@GlobalScope_Error>` **rename** **(** :ref:`String "
"<class_String>` from, :ref:`String <class_String>` to **)**"
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_directory.rst:250
msgid ""
"Renames (move) the ``from`` file to the ``to`` destination. Both "
"arguments should be paths to files, either relative or absolute. If the "
"destination file exists and is not access-protected, it will be "
"overwritten."
msgstr ""

